CS Kagwe reveals that 285 patients have recovered from the disease.The total recoveries in the country now stand at 75,559. Confirmed cases of Covid-19 in Kenya now stand at 94,151 after 390 people tested positive in the last 24 hours.
According to the Ministry of Health, the new cases are from a sample size of 6,277 with the cumulative tests in the country now at 1,003,493.
“From the cases 363 are Kenyans while 27 are foreigners with 265 being male and 125 being female. The youngest is a one year-old baby, while the oldest is 91,” Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kagwe said in a statement on Saturday.



