Kagwe also revealed that 285 patients have recovered from the disease with this figure comprising 242 patients who were on home-based care programme and 43 patients who have been discharged from various hospitals in the country.
The total recoveries in the country now stand at 75,559.
The CS said that four patients have succumbed to the disease in the last 24 hours, bringing the cumulative fatalities in the country to 1,633.



