According to CS Kagwe, there are 844 patients admitted in various health facilities countrywide and 5,916 on home-based isolation and care.
Out of this number, 52 patients are in the Intensive Care Unit (ICU), 24 of whom are on ventilatory support while 25 on supplemental oxygen. Three patients are on observation.
Another 28 patients are separately on supplementary oxygen out of whom 23 are in the general wards. Five patients are in the High Dependency Unit (HDU).










Nairobi County accounted for 103 of the new infections, followed by Mombasa 50, Nakuru 48, Kitui 27, Embu 20, Kilifi 15, Migori 13, Uasin Gishu 12, Laikipia 12, Murang'a 11, Kiambu 10 and Isiolo 10.
Other new cases were reported in Meru 9, Kakamega 8, Baringo 6, Busia 4, Nandi 4, Machakos 4, Garissa 4, Kisumu 3, Trans Nzoia 3, Siaya 2 Makueni 2 and Turkana 2.



